The paper deals with object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Focal Loss is a modification of the standard cross entropy loss used in deep learning models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the issue of class imbalance, which is a common problem in neural networks and can be addressed using techniques from neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method using metrics such as precision and recall, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL).
